star, if you know what I mean.

37:45.597 --> 37:49.165
- Please don't say that, I've
had my fill of stars lately.

37:49.268 --> 37:51.635
- Well not like that
honey, what Debbie means

37:51.737 --> 37:52.836
is he's respected.

37:52.938 --> 37:56.406
- A hero really, because
of Weston and all.

37:56.508 --> 37:59.309
- Having a kid makes
you a town hero?

37:59.411 --> 38:02.579
- Well in Luke's
case it kinda does.

38:02.681 --> 38:03.613
- A little bit.

38:09.454 --> 38:11.554
- Can we go ice skating
at the pond today?

38:12.524 --> 38:14.057
- I thought you
hated ice skating?

38:14.159 --> 38:15.492
- I kind of do.

38:15.594 --> 38:17.427
But I have to do an assignment
for Mrs. Brown's class.

38:17.529 --> 38:19.729
- Mrs. Brown told you you
need to go ice skating?

38:19.831 --> 38:22.499
- No, not really, but I
don't know what else to do.

38:22.601 --> 38:23.466
- Let me see that.

38:31.209 --> 38:33.943
Christmas is about more than
just time off from school

38:34.046 --> 38:37.614
and presents from Santa, but
what does it mean to you?

38:37.716 --> 38:39.449
Make your own version of
the 12 Days of Christmas

38:39.551 --> 38:41.618
with your own list of 12 things

38:41.720 --> 38:43.687
that matter most to
you this Christmas.

38:43.789 --> 38:44.954
Like ice skating?

38:47.225 --> 38:49.292
- I don't know, that's what
Kyle said he was doing,

38:49.394 --> 38:50.627
Sean too.

38:50.729 --> 38:52.796
- Listen if you want
to go ice skating

38:52.898 --> 38:54.230
we can we can go ice skating.

38:54.333 --> 38:58.635
But I think your teacher
wants you to pick something

38:58.737 --> 39:00.103
that's a little more meaningful.

39:00.205 --> 39:01.705
And unless you have
some secret life

39:01.807 --> 39:04.607
that I don't know about,
I'm sure we can find

39:04.710 --> 39:05.875
at least a dozens of things

39:05.977 --> 39:07.844
that would rate better
than that in your book.

39:08.914 --> 39:10.213
- Yeah this is why
I hate homework.

39:10.315 --> 39:11.448
- Yeah.

39:13.652 --> 39:15.051
We'll figure out something good.

39:20.025 --> 39:20.957
Hey you!

39:21.059 --> 39:21.758
- Hi.

39:21.860 --> 39:22.892
- Come on in.

39:24.563 --> 39:26.363
Let me get that for ya.

39:30.335 --> 39:31.735
- Thank you.

39:31.837 --> 39:33.503
- You're welcome, I see
Becky finished your car.

39:33.605 --> 39:35.605
- She did, and she was
every bit as brilliant

39:35.707 --> 39:36.639
as you said she'd be.

39:36.742 --> 39:38.208
- Yeah she something, after you.

39:39.711 --> 39:42.445
- Wow, you have
a beautiful home.

39:42.547 --> 39:44.948
- Thanks, and it's
a work in progress.

39:45.050 --> 39:45.949
- I don't know what
you're talking about,

39:46.051 --> 39:47.350
I think it's beautiful.

39:50.756 --> 39:51.688
- You remember Weston.

39:51.790 --> 39:52.922
- I do, hi Weston.

39:53.024 --> 39:53.690
- Hi.

39:53.792 --> 39:55.258
- Something wrong?

39:55.360 --> 39:57.293
- Oh he's just moody
over a school project

39:57.396 --> 39:58.128
that he has to do.

39:58.230 --> 40:00.196
- I see, what's the project?

40:03.535 --> 40:06.169
Wow, Mrs. Brown.

40:06.271 --> 40:08.805
Wait I remember this, I had to
do this when I was your age.

40:08.907 --> 40:10.507
I can't believe
she's still teaching.

40:10.609 --> 40:11.674
- Yeah she's ancient.

40:11.777 --> 40:13.643
- That's what I thought
at your age too.

40:13.745 --> 40:15.278
I can help you if you want?

40:15.380 --> 40:17.180
- Yeah, do you want
to give me yours?

40:17.282 --> 40:19.682
- I don't know about that,
but I'd be happy to help you

40:19.785 --> 40:20.817
make your own.

40:20.919 --> 40:21.885
- I guess that's fine.

40:21.987 --> 40:23.219
- Weston!

40:23.321 --> 40:24.020
- What?

40:24.122 --> 40:24.821
- Say thank you.

40:24.923 --> 40:25.688
- For what?

40:25.791 --> 40:27.223
We haven't done anything yet.

40:27.325 --> 40:28.391
- Kid's got a point.

40:28.493 --> 40:29.959
- I'm trying to set
a good example here.

40:30.061 --> 40:31.461
- You are.

40:31.563 --> 40:32.462
- Shall we get started?

40:32.564 --> 40:33.963
- Yes.

40:34.065 --> 40:36.833
Okay so Shirley assures me
that there are plenty of people

40:36.935 --> 40:39.702
excited to perform, so
that makes me feel better.

40:39.805 --> 40:41.204
- Yeah me too.

40:41.306 --> 40:42.639
- No, you should definitely
be up there with your guitar.

40:42.741 --> 40:45.141
- No, no, no, no, no,
I am happy to help out

40:45.243 --> 40:48.311
in any way that I can,
but I have no desire to be

40:48.413 --> 40:49.579
up on that stage.

40:49.681 --> 40:52.582
Music for me is more, personal.

40:52.684 --> 40:55.718
It's my therapy in a way,
and I don't feel right

40:55.821 --> 40:58.822
being in the spotlight,
does any of that make sense?

40:59.825 --> 41:02.258
- It makes all the
sense in the world.

41:04.996 --> 41:07.897
- It's Shirley,
sorry one second.

41:09.367 --> 41:10.133
Hello.

41:11.837 --> 41:12.902
Hey.

41:13.004 --> 41:15.705
- So, do you have any
ideas for the project?

41:15.807 --> 41:17.874
- Not really, I asked Luke
about going ice skating

41:17.976 --> 41:19.809
but he thinks we can do better.

41:20.846 --> 41:22.612
Why do we have homework
over Christmas break?

41:22.714 --> 41:24.113
It's entirely unfair.

41:24.216 --> 41:25.748
- Well I agree.

41:25.851 --> 41:28.117
But I bet we can figure
out something really good.

41:28.220 --> 41:30.620
- That's exactly what Luke said.

41:30.722 --> 41:34.591
- Alright, so, apparently
one of the pipes

41:34.693 --> 41:38.461
in Shirley's house broke
and everything is flooding.

41:38.563 --> 41:41.197
- Yikes, wait she
called you about that?

41:41.299 --> 41:42.465
- He's the guy everyone calls,

41:42.567 --> 41:44.734
he's basically
the town handyman.

41:44.836 --> 41:46.870
- I hate to do this
but can we reschedule?

41:46.972 --> 41:47.737
- Of course.

41:47.839 --> 41:49.138
- Thank you.

41:49.241 --> 41:50.306
Weston get your coat.

41:50.408 --> 41:51.541
- No, I don't wanna go.

41:51.643 --> 41:52.976
- Come on hurry up.

41:53.078 --> 41:54.611
- Why can't I just stay here.

41:54.713 --> 41:56.112
- You know I can't
leave you by yourself.

41:56.214 --> 41:57.747
- I'm not by myself.

41:57.849 --> 41:58.548
- Weston.

41:58.650 --> 41:59.816
- I can stay with him.

41:59.918 --> 42:01.217
- I can't ask you to do that.

42:01.319 --> 42:04.287
- You didn't I offered,
it's really not a problem,

42:04.389 --> 42:06.523
we can get a start on
Mrs. Brown's project.

42:07.893 --> 42:09.425
- Alright if you don't mind.

42:09.528 --> 42:10.927
- I really don't.

42:11.029 --> 42:11.861
- Thank you.

42:14.900 --> 42:17.934
There's lasagna and a
half a roast chicken here

42:18.036 --> 42:21.271
in the fridge, along with
there's plenty of roast veggies

42:21.373 --> 42:22.772
that you can just heat up.

42:22.874 --> 42:24.474
Mi casa es Su casa

42:24.576 --> 42:25.275
- Awesome.

42:25.377 --> 42:26.509
- Great.

42:26.611 --> 42:29.479
Oh first aid kit, right
here in the cabinet.

42:29.581 --> 42:31.681
Let me take it out, just
so you know where it is.

42:31.783 --> 42:33.750
- We're fine, go.

42:33.852 --> 42:34.918
Is he always like this?

42:35.020 --> 42:36.352
- Always.

42:36.454 --> 42:38.321
- Let me give you my phone
number just so you have it.

42:38.423 --> 42:40.290
- I have it, you gave me
your address remember?

42:40.392 --> 42:43.326
- Right, right, let
me give you the number

42:43.428 --> 42:44.794
to the town sheriff.

42:44.896 --> 42:46.829
- Seriously, go, help Shirley,

42:46.932 --> 42:48.298
her house is
flooding as we speak.

42:48.400 --> 42:49.532
- Good point.

42:54.439 --> 42:55.204
Okay.

42:56.241 --> 42:57.774
Okay, thank you.

43:01.913 --> 43:04.280
- Wow I cannot
believe that worked.

43:04.382 --> 43:05.748
- What do you mean?

43:05.850 --> 43:09.919
- Luke's uptight, he
doesn't really trust anyone.

43:10.021 --> 43:11.955
This means he trusts you.

43:15.093 --> 43:17.660
- Do you always call him Luke?

43:17.762 --> 43:19.062
- What else would I call him?

43:19.965 --> 43:20.897
- Dad?

43:20.999 --> 43:22.832
- Oh, Luke's not my dad.

43:22.934 --> 43:24.000
- He's not?

43:24.102 --> 43:26.469
- He's my uncle, my
dad died awhile ago.

43:27.439 --> 43:28.705
- I'm so sorry.

43:28.807 --> 43:30.740
- It's cool, he's a good
uncle, but he's definitely

43:30.842 --> 43:32.375
in denial about my manhood.

43:33.945 --> 43:35.211
- What?

43:35.313 --> 43:37.013
- You heard me, he thinks
of me as this little kid

43:37.115 --> 43:38.815
he has to take
care of constantly.

43:38.917 --> 43:40.917
You saw it just now, but
honestly, I'm the one

43:41.019 --> 43:41.951
taking care of him.

43:43.254 --> 43:44.988
True story.

43:45.090 --> 43:48.224
- I see, well he's
very lucky to have you.

43:49.194 --> 43:50.627
- We're lucky to
have each other.

43:51.963 --> 43:53.930
- Alright, what do you say we
start tackling this project?

43:54.032 --> 43:55.131
- Sure.

44:14.052 --> 44:15.051
- Hello?

44:18.123 --> 44:19.155
Weston!

44:21.926 --> 44:22.825
What's this?

44:22.927 --> 44:23.993
- What do you think?

44:24.095 --> 44:26.496
Just working on some
stuff for the project.

44:27.465 --> 44:28.798
- Where's Harmony?

44:28.900 --> 44:30.900
- She's here, she's getting
some construction paper.

44:31.002 --> 44:32.235
I told her where it was.

44:37.442 --> 44:38.207
- Aha!

44:40.979 --> 44:41.878
- What are you doing?

44:41.980 --> 44:43.112
- Oh hey you're back.

44:43.214 --> 44:44.213
- What are you doing with this?

44:44.315 --> 44:45.448
- Oh I was just trying
to get some paper.

44:45.550 --> 44:48.151
- Oh, yeah there's
no paper in here.

44:48.253 --> 44:50.353
- No I know it was underneath.

44:50.455 --> 44:52.789
- Listen thank you so
much for watching Weston

44:52.891 --> 44:54.957
but I got it from here,
I'll walk you out.

44:56.561 --> 44:57.360
- Okay.

45:01.900 --> 45:03.299
- Goodnight.

45:22.520 --> 45:24.520
- And that's when I told him
we had better do whatever

45:24.622 --> 45:26.923
it takes to find that
doll before Christmas.

45:29.928 --> 45:33.029
- That just made me very
afraid of when Emily

45:33.131 --> 45:35.098
starts asking for
specific dolls.

45:35.200 --> 45:36.265
- As you should be!

45:36.367 --> 45:38.334
Treasure these early
years while you can.

45:39.170 --> 45:41.037
- Are you bringing her to
Herman's big send-off on Friday?

45:41.139 --> 45:44.841
- Oh yes, We found
her the cutest

45:44.943 --> 45:46.342
Christmas sweater
and everything.

45:46.444 --> 45:48.678
- Leave it to Shirley to
make a Bora Bora sendoff

45:48.780 --> 45:50.680
party Christmas sweater themed.

45:52.183 --> 45:54.383
- I can't believe
Herman is leaving.

45:54.486 --> 45:56.085
I've missed so much.

45:56.187 --> 45:58.054
- Well you know, that's life.

45:58.156 --> 46:00.356
You had your own dreams,
but we are thrilled

46:00.458 --> 46:03.426
you're here now, we haven't
had a proper girls' night in

46:03.528 --> 46:04.927
I can't even tell you how long.

46:07.799 --> 46:09.132
- You know what though?

46:09.234 --> 46:12.535
I'm realizing, I don't think
that they were my dreams.

46:12.637 --> 46:17.473
I mean I gave so much of
myself to Devin, and for what?

46:17.575 --> 46:20.076
- Forget him, if he doesn't
know how special you are

46:20.178 --> 46:20.977
he doesn't deserve you.

46:21.079 --> 46:22.044
- Seriously.

46:22.147 --> 46:23.479
- And on that note,

46:25.083 --> 46:26.649
I hear you've been
spending a little time

46:26.751 --> 46:28.050
with the town stud.

46:28.153 --> 46:31.654
- Okay, I have heard
town star, town hero,

46:31.756 --> 46:33.489
and now the town stud?

46:33.591 --> 46:34.991
- Luke is all of those things.

46:35.093 --> 46:38.961
- Well great, I've upset the
town star, hero, stud then.

46:39.063 --> 46:40.263
- Upset him what?

46:40.365 --> 46:42.765
- Yeah I don't even
really know what happened?

46:42.867 --> 46:44.333
- Well?

46:44.435 --> 46:45.134
- Well what?

46:45.236 --> 46:47.003
- Well what did you do?

46:48.239 --> 46:50.072
- I was helping Weston
with a project while Luke

46:50.175 --> 46:52.108
was out I don't
know helping Shir.

46:52.210 --> 46:54.343
- What do you mean out?

46:54.445 --> 46:57.013
- He left you alone with Weston?

46:57.115 --> 46:58.981
- Yeah, is that a big deal?

46:59.083 --> 47:00.983
- Go on tell us the rest.

47:01.085 --> 47:01.918
- Okay.

47:03.321 --> 47:05.321
So I went upstairs to find
some paper and then Luke

47:05.423 --> 47:08.724
got home and saw me holding
this box by the hall closet

47:08.827 --> 47:12.862
and got all weird, and
he kinda kicked me out.

47:13.731 --> 47:15.198
- Wait that's it?

47:15.300 --> 47:17.834
He saw you holding
some box by the closet?

47:17.936 --> 47:18.701
- That's it.

47:20.438 --> 47:21.604
- Oh!

47:21.706 --> 47:25.074
Okay, I think I know
what's going on here.

47:26.144 --> 47:27.977
Get your coats let's go.

47:31.216 --> 47:32.148
- Harmony.

47:32.250 --> 47:32.949
- Hi.

47:33.051 --> 47:34.317
- Hey.

47:34.419 --> 47:35.251
- Shh.

47:39.424 --> 47:41.190
- What are you doing here?

47:41.292 --> 47:44.360
- I don't actually really know.

47:44.462 --> 47:46.229
- What is she doing?

47:46.331 --> 47:47.530
- Shh, shh.

47:47.632 --> 47:49.198
- I'm sorry about earlier.

47:49.300 --> 47:51.567
You didn't do anything
wrong, I just.

47:51.669 --> 47:53.135
- Ooh!

47:54.272 --> 47:56.372
- Oh, hey guys, how are you?

47:56.474 --> 47:58.007
- Hi!

47:58.109 --> 48:00.243
Hello it's so good to see you.

48:00.345 --> 48:02.144
Harmony, I didn't
know you'd be here.

48:02.247 --> 48:05.147
We were just out for a
little stroll in the area.

48:05.250 --> 48:08.184
All together, by the way,
really like what you've done

48:08.286 --> 48:09.752
with those hedges.

48:09.854 --> 48:10.887
- It's beautiful.

48:10.989 --> 48:12.655
- Oh look, here's
where I left my car.

48:12.757 --> 48:13.823
- Wait, guys.

48:14.659 --> 48:15.892
- Stay warm, bye bye.

48:18.196 --> 48:19.195
- Guys!

48:24.135 --> 48:25.401
- What was that about?

48:26.471 --> 48:28.504
- I think we all
just turned 13 again.

48:30.008 --> 48:33.242
Must be something in the air.

48:33.344 --> 48:34.744
- Yeah I don't follow.

48:36.014 --> 48:37.747
- It's a girl thing.

48:37.849 --> 48:39.982
I think I should get going too.

48:40.952 --> 48:42.518
- Didn't your ride
just leave you?

48:43.488 --> 48:45.087
- Yes, yes she did.

48:46.858 --> 48:48.090
- I can give you a ride.

48:48.192 --> 48:50.293
- No, no, you know what,
I think I'll just walk.

48:50.395 --> 48:52.228
It's nice out.

48:52.330 --> 48:53.095
- I'll walk you home then.

48:53.197 --> 48:55.031
- No, you have Weston, please.

48:55.133 --> 48:57.266
- What I can't walk a
beautiful woman home?

48:59.137 --> 49:01.704
- I didn't mean that.

49:01.806 --> 49:05.041
- Actually Weston is with
his friend Kyle tonight.

49:05.143 --> 49:06.008
Let me get my coat.

49:07.578 --> 49:08.244
- Okay.

49:18.189 --> 49:19.221
- After you.

49:24.862 --> 49:26.462
When did you move away?

49:27.999 --> 49:31.734
- Gosh, 10 years ago,
it's been awhile.

49:33.338 --> 49:37.406
I used to visit pretty often,
but then my mom passed away.

49:38.743 --> 49:41.210
It's just been kinda
hard to come back.

49:41.312 --> 49:44.880
It doesn't feel like
home without her.

49:46.451 --> 49:47.216
- I'm sorry.

49:49.087 --> 49:50.052
- You know I realized though,

49:50.154 --> 49:52.588
that it hasn't been
fair to my dad.

49:54.926 --> 49:56.492
I know I've neglected him.

49:57.795 --> 50:00.396
He started dating Debbie
and I couldn't handle it.

50:01.265 --> 50:02.498
Not that there's anything
wrong with Debbie,

50:02.600 --> 50:06.435
she's actually really
lovely I just, miss my mom.

50:11.542 --> 50:13.442
When did you move to Miracle?

50:13.544 --> 50:14.710
Tell me about you, yeah.

50:14.812 --> 50:17.513
- Me, God about
five years ago now.

50:18.750 --> 50:20.349
- That's right when
I stopped visiting.

50:20.451 --> 50:21.384
- Really?

50:21.486 --> 50:22.451
- Yeah.

50:22.553 --> 50:23.319
- Shame.

50:27.392 --> 50:28.457
- What brought you here?

50:30.428 --> 50:32.261
- Well I think you
already know part of this.

50:32.363 --> 50:35.898
And that is that
Weston isn't my son.

50:38.236 --> 50:42.872
I mean, he's legally mine,
but I'm not his real dad.

50:44.175 --> 50:46.375
- Yeah, Weston did mention that.

50:46.477 --> 50:50.212
- Yeah, yeah, he was
my brother's kid.

50:50.314 --> 50:53.382
And when he was born, his
mom, well she took off.

50:54.452 --> 50:58.220
Ad my brother when he passed,
I became his legal guardian,

50:59.490 --> 51:00.423
per David's wishes.

51:00.525 --> 51:01.991
And mine of course.

51:02.093 --> 51:04.560
And hopefully Weston's.

51:04.662 --> 51:08.497
- Weston told me that he
feels very lucky to have you.

51:08.599 --> 51:09.565
- No, I'm the lucky one.

51:11.169 --> 51:12.268
He's a good kid.

51:15.373 --> 51:18.074
And David, David
was a great dad.

51:18.176 --> 51:20.042
David was a great guy,

51:20.144 --> 51:24.547
and I know I fall
short of that everyday.

51:24.649 --> 51:27.783
- I can assure you
that is not true.

51:27.885 --> 51:29.852
I see what you do for
Weston and for this town

51:29.954 --> 51:34.957
and I can't even begin to
explain how in awe of you I am.

51:43.301 --> 51:45.034
- Hey where'd you go?

51:45.136 --> 51:46.268
Everything okay?

51:46.370 --> 51:47.536
- Yeah, yeah.

51:53.211 --> 51:58.214
So I've been so upset about
this guy that I knew was

52:03.321 --> 52:05.488
I guess I thought was the one.

52:06.557 --> 52:09.258
But I don't know, I
look at you and the way

52:09.360 --> 52:13.295
that you love Weston,
and my dad and Debbie.

52:13.397 --> 52:18.267
And the girls and
how happy they are.

52:18.369 --> 52:21.570
And I realize I never had that.

52:24.575 --> 52:28.944
I thought that I had to
get away from this town

52:29.046 --> 52:33.182
to be happy, and to
figure things out.

52:35.353 --> 52:37.419
And I've done neither
of those things

52:37.522 --> 52:39.255
by being away from Miracle.

52:40.725 --> 52:41.824
In fact all I've really done

52:41.926 --> 52:43.692
is neglect the
people that I love.

52:46.430 --> 52:48.197
Wow I'm sorry, that was a lot.

52:53.137 --> 52:56.372
- I know I don't know you
that well, but I'd say

52:56.474 --> 52:58.474
you've got the really
important parts,

52:58.576 --> 53:00.042
very much figured out.

53:02.280 --> 53:03.712
Weston doesn't just
take to anybody the way

53:03.814 --> 53:05.181
that he takes to you.

